## download the conda from https://bioconda.github.io/
## in linux execute
sh Miniconda2-latest-Linux-x86_64.sh
## there will be a list of yes or no in the follwoing, all enter yes and press enter
## the installation will create the directory in the home path
## the installation will modify the .bashrc file to set the environment
source ~/.bashrc
## then the conda command can be used

## use conda to install some software





